<h1 id="competitions">Competitions</h1>
 <h2>How do I pick a competition winner</h2>
 <p>Once your competition is closed - you will be able to pick a single winner. You must do so with 14 days* of the close date.</p>
 <ol>
   <li>Locate the winning design on your competition page, in the Entries or Client Faves tab.</li>
   <li>Select the winning logo.</li>
   <li>An email will automatically be sent to the winner, asking them to upload artwork.</li>
   <li>Once the artwork has been uploaded - you will be able to download it.</li>
   <li>Provided the designer has uploaded the artwork file, we'll pay the designer automatically between 7-14 days after the competition close.</li>
   <li>Clients have 7 days after the close date to raise a complaint about the supplied artwork.</li>
   <li>If there is a dispute about artwork quality, Logosauce admins will inspect artwork and arbitrate accordingly.</li>
 </ol>
   <p>* Logosauce will send you a reminder to choose a winner after the close date.</p>  
 <br />
 <h2>What happens if I fail to or can't pick a winner after 14 days</h2>
 <p>You must pick a winner within 14 days as per the Logosauce competition rules. There are no exceptions. Failure to pick a winner will result in an incomplete competition, you will forfeit your prize-money and any fees and you will not receive artwork.</p>
 <br />
 <h3>Error message:  "Permission denied, your account is too new to enter this competition"</h3>
 <p>Logosauce prohibits users from entering a competition that started before you became a member.</p>
 <br />
 <h3>Error message: "Permission denied, you must first register your Paypal account to enter competition"</h3>
 <p>Prizemoney is paid to winners via Paypal. We do not pay using any other method. To avoid problems later and to avoid disappointment, we ask all designers to record their Paypal details before they can enter a competition. Click the My Profile tab, Edit and add your Paypal email to your profile.</p>
 <br />
 <h2>When do competition winners get paid?</h2>
 <p>Competition winners will get paid approximately 7 days after they have uploaded finished art for the client to collect. The 7 days stand-down period gives the client 7 days to complain if there is a problem with the artwork. Once the winner is selected - the winner is emailed. The onus is then on the winner to work with the client and upload finished artwork to the winning logo.</p>
