<h1 id="projects">Projects (NEW)</h1>
<h2>How is a project different from a competition?</h2>
<p>A project enables a client to work with one designer (as opposed to receiving designs from many designers in a competition). Essentially designers bid for a project and a client awards a contract to one designer and then works with them to complete the project.</p>
<br />
<h2>What does a project cost?</h2>
<p>A client can advertise a project for US$50.  It's free for designers to bid on projects and there is NO success fee. The listing fee for the client is the only cost.</p>
<h2>Do designers win points for a successful bid?</h2>
<p>Yes each winning bid is awarded 100 points - which are added to the designers profile.</p>

