<h1 id="people">People</h1>
<h2 id="pro">Pro Designer accounts</h2>
<id ="pro"><h3>What's a <span class="pro">Pro</span> Designer account?</h3>
<p>If you're a designer, you can also apply for a <em>Pro Designer</em> account which gives you added benefits including ability to sell logos, receive invites for pro only events, and your comments and votes will have greater weight. <br /><br />Pro accounts cost $50 and are approved by Logosauce admins before being accepted.  Once you've completed sign-up and logged in, you'll need to upload some of your work, and complete a profile bio so that we can review your suitability for the Pro status.</p>
<br />
<h3>Who is a Pro Designer account suitable for?</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Professional designers working full or part time in a design business or freelancing</li>
  <li>Design firms.</li>
  <li>Designer with at least 10 high quality designs of their own making uploaded to their portfolio.</li>
  <li>Logosauce designers with a proven track record on Logosauce and a portfolio with at least 10 quality designs.</li>
</ul>
<p>Note: Logosauce designers who have won 2 or more design competitions get automatic Pro status (free of charge).</p>  

<h3>What does a Pro Designer account cost.?</h3>
<p>$50 application fee (non refundable) <em>or FREE(see below)</em>.<br /><br />Logosauce admins will review your portfolio and bio and any links to ascertain your suitability for Pro status. We're looking for your ability to create professional well thought out designs and satisfy client needs.</p>
<h3>Benefits of a Pro Designer account.</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Higher profile on Logosauce.</li>
  <li>Your opinion is valued above a standard designer. Each vote a Pro makes is worth triple the points of a standard designer.</li>
  <li>You'll appear in exclusive Pro Designer listings.</li>
  <li>More enquiries and better results.</li>
</ol>
<h3>How do I get a Pro account?</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Win 2 or more competitions. You will be automatically be upgraded to a Pro account free of charge.</li>
  OR
  <li>Pay a $50 application fee and Logosauce will inspect your portfolio and credentials for suitability. You need at least 10 quality designs of your own making in your portfolio and a completed Bio and contact details.
    <ol>
      <li>Prepare your Portfolio and complete your Bio.</li>
      <li>Click your My Profile tab.</li>
      <li>Click the Edit link in top right hand side of your details panel.</li>
      <li>Click the <em>Upgrade to pro designer</em> link.</li>
      <li>Pay your application fee.</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <p>You can apply at any-time. Just ensure you have at least 10 good quality designs in your portfolio and have completed your bio.</p>
