<h1 id="blog">Blog</h1>
<h2>Can I comment on the blog?</h2>
<p>Yes provided you are signed-in.</p>
<h2>How can I start a discussion?</h2>
<p>Logosauce does not have a forum and users do not have permissions to post new blog articles. However you can email us, and suggest a topic for a blog article or even write one and send it to us for inclusion at the discretion of Logosauce admins.</p>
<hr />


<h1 id="myprofile">My Profile</h1>
<h2>Can I change my details?</h2>
<p>Yes - just sign-in. The <em>My Profile</em> tab will appear, click the tab and then the <em>Edit</em> link to change your details.</p> 
<h2>How do I close my account?</h2>
<p>Go to your <em>My Profile</em> page, click the <em>Edit</em> link and then the <em>Cancel my account</em> link at the bottom right of the Edit page. Note, while your account will be cancelled and you will no longer ben able to access anything, your data may not be entirely deleted, because we need to retain some data for some of your previous activity, such as competition entries, etc.</p>
<hr />

<h1 id="other">Other</h1>
<h2>What is Textile ?</h2>
<p>Logosauce uses <a href="http://redcloth.org/hobix.com/textile">Textile</a>, a simple markup language, becoming popular on many websites, for many of it's user entered text areas. With Textile you can style your entries without having to use HTML.<br /><br />For example to create a bulleted list, add an *  in front of a line of text or a # for a number list.<br /><br />We provide a link to a Textile guide where textile is available.</p>
<h2>How do I report an inappropriate listing or feedback ?</h2>
<p>Please email <a href="mailto:support@logosauce.com">Logosauce Help</a> with your concern and where possible include links to the offending materials by navigating to the logo or profile you are referring to and then copy the URL in your browser's address bar and paste into your message.  Upon receipt LogoSauce will inspect the logo and take action where necessary.</p>
